<div class="row"><!-- ID:1} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Kyle Knobloch</strong></div><img src="/img/car1.JPG" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Lead Webmaster, Programmer and Marketing</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Junior </h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Kyle started in his sophomore year of High School. He helped program the robot and developed the website from scratch last year. He was able to make the team look more professional with his website design. He was also played a key role during Engineering Week for the local elementary school. This year he plans on making the website even better, help with robot code, and promote the team. He's currently a lifeguard at two local pools, coaches a middle school Water Polo team, and volunteers regularly at multiple organizations. He has worked on filming multiple town hall meetings and even helped film the Plymouth Thanksgiving Parade. He's currently taking AP Computer Science and is looking into an programming independent study in his Junior year second semester. He's also a multiple Best of the Bunch reward recipient, SUMMA recipient, and an honors student. Kyle is very interested in entering a career in one of the STEM fields. He's looking into schools such as Waterloo, RIT, and Carleton and plans on majoring in Computer Science.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:2} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Teddy Stahl</strong></div><img src="/img/car1.JPG" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Fabrication Team Member</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Freshman </h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Teddy is starting his first year with the DHS robotics, but this is not his first time on a robotics team. In his first year with the DMS robotics team, the team's robot received an honorary mention from the First Lego League thanks to his contributions. Teddy spent three years total in the Duxbury Middle School First Lego League team. In his spare time, he enjoys jogging, as well as studying news and politics with the high school's Global Engagement Club. He also volunteers at the middle school to help the robotics team. From time to time, Teddy will see a lecture in Rhode Island at the Watson institute, and he has gone to the iDtech camps for many years in order to create a video game in one week. He has built his own computer and loves to use it to play high graphic video games. Teddy is an aspiring console inventor, creative director of video games, and hopeful multibillionaire.
</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:16} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Chase Jamieson</strong></div><img src="{}}][hghgvh" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Control Systems Manager; Member of the Fabrication Team</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Senior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Chase is beginning his first year as part of the robotics team and has had experience coding for two years. This year, he has been given the responsibility of being one of the lead coders and one of the members of the fabrication team. Chase is enthralled to be starting his first year with these responsibilities and to be learning more about the fabrication process. During the rest of the year, Chase is rowing on Duxbury Bay and training for a successful rowing career, and in the summer, he can be found teaching kids how to kayak, paddleboard, and row at Duxbury Bay Maritime School. Chase also has an intense passion for computers; he has built one for himself and many of his friends.  At the moment, Chase is working hard now to prepare for a very successful season for himself and his peers.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div></div><div class="row"<!-- ID:17} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Griffin Brayer</strong></div><img src="gmgjdjd" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Pneumatics System Manager</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Senior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">This is the first year that Griffin has been on the robotics team. He is part of the sailing team during the fall and spring, as well as the swim team during the winter. Griffin has been sailing for four years, and has been on varsity for the past two years. Griffin is currently working on finishing his Eagle Project in order to earn the rank of Eagle Scout. Griffin plays bass clarinet in the Duxbury High School Wind Ensemble and Symphony Orchestra, and he participated in the Southeastern District Senior Music Festival his sophomore year. He also plays clarinet in the pep band, and synthesizer for the pit orchestra. He is planning on going into the field of electrical and computer engineering.
</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:19} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Ben Rosenberger</strong></div><img src="fryhijtg" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Electrical Systems Manager</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Senior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Ben joined the team sophomore year during the team's rookie year. He helped to build and construct the electronics on the robot. During his second year he continued to work on the electronics design and all of the control systems on the robot. He also helped when the team won their first competition at UMass Dartmouth during their 2015 season. Finally, in his senior year he serves as the electronics director and oversees all of the electronics work on the robot, as we seek out to win another competition.
</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:20} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Matt Antonino</strong></div><img src="rhogfsvnofs" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Director of Systems Operations; Captain</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Senior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Matt has been a member of the team for 3 years, he is a founding member and loves to do robotics. He feels that it is truly a passion of his and hopes to possibly pursue it in the future as a career, and study mechanical engineering in college. As Director of Systems Operations, he oversees the manufacturing and construction of the robot and works with the mentors to see that the project is completed in a timely and well done manner. He has always enjoyed working on the robot so he also assists the manufacturing team to complete the robot.
</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:21} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>George Williams</strong></div><img src="sfjk" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Lead Scout</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Junior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">George joined Duxbury Robotics in his freshman year, and became the team’s Lead Scout this year. His duties include watching and evaluating other teams at competitions. Outside of robotics, George is involved in student council, serves on the award committee, and is involved in Boy Scouts. He became an Eagle Scout, the highest rank one can achieve, at the age of thirteen. For athletics, George rows at the Duxbury Bay Maritime School in the spring and fall and wrestles at Duxbury High School in the winter. George hopes that robotics will prepare for a future of becoming an orthopedic and prosthetic surgeon.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:22} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Michael Gill</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Lead Scout; Videographer</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Junior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Michael started with the team as a freshman during the team's rookie year.  He has helped on many of the different aspects of the team.  This year, he has attained two separate leadership positions on the team; Michael is the Lead Scout and Videographer for team 4908.  He has big plans to boost the scouting program and the team’s relationships with other teams at competitions, as well as develop and reveal promotional videos for the team and the robot. In his free time, Michael can be found taking long walks on the beach, admiring the sunset and eating ice cream. He is also a leader on the school wrestling team, and one of the captains for the spring track team. He plays Euphonium in the high school band, and is very excited to continue to be a part of the amazing FRC program for his remaining years at Duxbury High School.
</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:23} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Juliana Ivanof</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Copy Editor; Sponsorship Coordinator</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Junior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Juliana Ivanof is a junior at DHS, and this is her first year joining the robotics team. After attending an FRC Competition last spring, she fell in love with the kind and generous atmosphere surrounding the world of robotics and felt compelled to add her name to Duxbury's roster. This year she will serve as one of the sponsorship coordinators and the copy editor, as well as learning how to use the CAD software. Outside of robotics, she is heavily involved both music and rowing. She plays flute in the school's highest ensemble group and the pit orchestra. In addition, she teaches younger students and plays in a South Shore flute choir. She has been a varsity coxswain on the crew team for 3 seasons and loves spending her time on Duxbury Bay with her teammates. She is excited to learn the ins and outs of robotics and become a valuable team player as the season goes on.
</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:24} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Harrison Price</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Electrical Systems Manager; Crew Chief</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Junior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Harrison started with the Duxbury Robotics team as a freshman during its rookie year, and has loved it ever since. As a freshman, he helped out with the build, and was a member of the scouting team at the competitions. Harrison has been volunteering with FIRST since he started on the team. He fell in love with volunteering at the second competition the team went to, when he volunteered at a safety goggle distribution table by an entrance. His sophomore year, he made sure to volunteer at every competition, this time as a member of the field reset team. Outside of the robotics team, Harrison does rowing year round and swimming in the winter. Harrison joined the Duxbury crew team in the fall of freshman year, and has done something rowing-related every season since. He is now on the varsity team, and plans to row in college. He started swimming in the winter of sophomore year, but is now doing crew in the winter of junior year. Harrison plans to continue robotics throughout his junior and senior year, and remain active with FIRST for the rest of his life. 
</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:25} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Matthew Rubin</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Promotional Director; Scout</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Junior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Matt began his robotics career as a freshman, when the team was just starting out. At first, he was on the fabrication team and helped out with building the robot. This year, he is more involved in business and marketing, designing the team’s apparel. He also scouts for the best teammates during the competitions. Between the ski team and his job, Matt puts as much time as he can into the program. Off season, Matt sails for his school and plays the snare drum for the football team in his school's pep band. He also works at his local summer camp where he clocks in 40 hours a week over the summer helping kids enjoy their time off of school.
</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:26} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Andrew Brook</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Promotional Director</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Junior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Andrew only recently started working with the Robotics team, but technology and computer engineering has always been a passion of his. Andrew has not had much experience with extracurricular programs, but has an open mind and is willing to help whenever it is needed. Andrew's main interest is computer science, and he has always been interested in learning new things about how different types of technology works. He is happy to be a part of the Robotics program, and hopes that whatever he can do will support the team and help win the competitions.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:27} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Colin Brown</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Marketing</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Junior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Colin started robotics as a sophomore, when team was in its second year and still growing. Colin works in business and reaches out to potential sponsors to get funding to keep the team going. The first year he did robotics, the was part of the winning alliance of the FRC UMass Dartmouth Recycle Rush.  Colin hopes to help the team carry on with funding so that the Duxbury robotics team will grow and continue to thrive. One day hoping for the Duxbury team to be well established and a prosperous team. Colin also does volunteer work for his church and goes New Orleans to build houses. Colin hopes that the STEM field will grow more into the mainstream education for youths to help in the near future.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:28} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Piers Klein</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Director of Operations</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Sophomore</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Piers is currently a sophomore at DHS. He was a founding member of Team 4908 in 2014 and has been active ever since. During the team’s first year, he became the lead scout and a drive coach in addition to responsibilities on the mechanical team. During the team’s second year, Piers served in a deputy role in the mechanical team and as a driver. In these positions, he gained experience in both working under stress and communicating ideas effectively and concisely. This year he can be found as the Director of Operations. Piers is also an active member of the school community. He is in his second year of sailing for the Varsity Sailing Team, plays the cello in the string ensemble, and is the Student Member of the Duxbury School Committee. In the future, he plans to continue his involvement with FIRST into adulthood and study engineering in college.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:29} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Lauren Willett</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Parts Manager; Photographer</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Sophomore</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Lauren is a sophomore at the high school. In addition to robotics, she is a member of the art club and has won several art awards throughout high school, including the DHS Summa Award for Visual Arts. She has also played piano from the age of 5 and can play by ear. She has been on the robotics team since freshman year and currently is the photographer and part manager for the team. Before high school, she was a both an individually competing figure skater and a member of a nationally competing figure skating team. She also enjoys rock climbing, astronomy, and any sort of learning.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:30} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Tara Curran</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Media Manager; Personnel Manager</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Sophomore</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">This year will be Tara's first year doing robotics club. She plans to help with the upkeep up all the teams social media to make sure that everybody is aware of what is going on with the team. Even though it is her first year, she is determined to quickly learn all about robotics and add to what she already learned from a robotics camp she went to at Harvard. Tara loves to row and can be found doing that when it is not robotics season. She also recently started swimming and is in the pit orchestra for the musical, so her winters are very busy with all three activities. Tara currently plays cello in Duxbury's String Ensemble. Aside from her other activities, Tara is excited to be a part of the robotics team this year and can't wait to contribute to the team by helping to make it as good as it can be.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:31} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Sage Pevzner</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Logistics Director; CAD Director</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Sophomore</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Sage started with the team as a freshman last year. Last year, he was a part of the electrical and pneumatics team and helped where he could (buttons, wire stripping, drilling holes, etc). This year Sage will be director of logistics, finding and ordering transportation for the team and robot to get to competitions. He will also be serving as the second CAD director, designing mechanisms and parts to go on the robot. In his free time, you could most likely find him at home, playing video games on the computer he built last year. Sage also enjoys creating digital art, some of which can be seen on display around the school.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:32} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Nathan Campbell</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Lead Fabricator; Sponsorship Coordinator</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Sophomore</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Nathan started robotics in the 2014/2015 season because he heard about it through his friends. During that year, he didn't really have a specific job, so he just helped out with whatever job needed to get done. He recently discovered an interest in metal fabrication and welding, so this year he will be a fabricator for the team. In his spare time, he and his friends made a functioning go kart from scratch that reached a top speed of 47mph. He has his own small metal working shop with welders and a forge for blacksmithing. This year he will be using these tools to complete whatever small tasks the team needs.
</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:33} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Brendan Sheehan</strong></div><img src="asdfghjkl" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Control Systems Manager</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Sophomore</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Brendan has been with the team for two years, working as a programmer for both years. Brendan is a total computer nerd and enjoys just about anything computer related. You can almost guarantee that if he's not playing video games in his free time, he is programming. He's been working with code for almost 7 years, but has the most experience in Java or C++. He is also a novice web designer, working on the Robotics site as well as his own.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:35} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Andrew Russo</strong></div><img src="bkhuieh" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Integration Coordinator</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Sophomore</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Andrew is a sophomore at Duxbury High School. This is his first year on the robotics team. During the spring and fall seasons, he is on the sailing team. He also enjoys sailing his friend’s catamaran and going to the beach in the summer. When he is not in school, he generally enjoys playing video games. Andrew's favorite classes in school are his programming classes. Next year, he hopes to take the AP Programming class.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:37} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>James Cipolletti</strong></div><img src="ojeniunriuv" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">CAD and Mechanical Director</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Sophomore</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">James Cipolletti is a sophomore who has been on the Duxbury Robotics team for 3 years. He has helped with the design and construction all 3 years, and he participated as a regular member of the pit and scouting team during the numerous competitions. Last year, James worked on the active intake system as well as creating 3D printed parts for the robot with the CAD software. This year, he has done the majority of the design work in PTC Creo CAD software, which includes our custom chassis and other superstructure elements. Also, he is serving as Drive Systems Manager which entails basic overview of the chassis and its constituent parts. Besides robotics, which tends to take up 99% of James' life during build season, James enjoys sailing on the Duxbury Sailing Team during the spring and fall seasons. Also, during the summer, he likes to build foam-board planes, rockets, and even a go kart with his friends (fellow robotics members).</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:38} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Jonathan Stordy</strong></div><img src="gbbyhyj" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Pneumatics System Manager</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Sophomore</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Jonathan Stordy is a sophomore at Duxbury High School. He moved to Duxbury in the summer before freshman year. This is his first year on the Robotics team, and he wants to continue on the team in the coming years. In his free time, Jonathan enjoys cycling.  He has played baseball since he was in second grade, and he played the trombone in middle school. He is looking forward to helping create a succeeding robot in the next two years before he graduates. </p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:39} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Billy Siegener</strong></div><img src="gbujbuinuo" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Lead Fabricator; Director of Purchasing; CAD Team Member</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Sophomore</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Billy started on the team when he was in eighth grade, during the team’s rookie year. This is his third year on the team, and he will be the Lead Fabricator, Director of Purchasing, and a member of the CAD Team. He currently knows the programming java, and is progressing with it while taking the AP Computer Science class. Outside of school, he and his friends work on things like building functioning go-karts and rockets from scratch. Also, during the spring and fall seasons, he is a part of the DHS Sailing Team, at the Duxbury Bay Maritime School.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:40} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
