                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Fabrication Team Member</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Freshman</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Giovanna Henry is a freshman at Duxbury High School. She has been doing robotics since sixth grade and has had an interest in robotics since she was very young. Seventh grade was her first year in participating in an FLL First Robotics Competition and she joined the team again in eighth grade. This year will be Giovanna's first time competing in a First FRC competition. Giovanna Henry also volunteers at the Duxbury Middle School Robotics Club to help them with their competition. She also volunteers at the Duxbury Free Library organizing and shelving books. She has been doing martial arts since she was in fifth grade and is now a brown belt. In seventh grade, she won the Tracy Bicknell Humanitarian Award for human kindness.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:42} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
                               <div class="panel panel-default">
                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Jack Champagne</strong></div><img src="kinifjrof" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Drive Systems Manager; Spirit Team Member</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Freshman</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">This year, Jack Champagne started on the high school robotics team. In the past, Jack has worked on the middle school robotics team since it started in 2013. This year, he helps out on the high school team and suggests ideas to incorporate into the chassis of the robot. On the drive systems team, he gets to see how all the parts of the robot fit together into the final product. He first found his interest in the high school robotics club when he built a home computer for himself. After school, Jack enjoys taking part in the high school ski team, tae kwon do at the Hanover YMCA, and the high school Lacrosse team.</p>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div>
                               </div><!-- ID:43} Type: 1--><div class="col-lg-4">
